1. Are you using emulated prepared statements or not? (`PDO::ATTR_EMULATE_PREPARES`/`PDO::MYSQL_ATTR_DIRECT_QUERY`)
2. Which MariaDB version you're using?

This store is covered by integration tests so it's definitely working with some version & configuration.

For the fix, instead of double-binding and double-encoding (and decoding on DB side) it could also be fixed within SQL which should have better performance:

```sql
INSERT INTO %1$s (id, metadata, `%2$s`)
VALUES (:id, @metadata := :metadata, @vector := VEC_FromText(:vector))
ON DUPLICATE KEY UPDATE metadata = @metadata, `%2$s` = @vector
```

